.TH ELKIRC 1 "8 December 2025" "elkirc 0.1" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
elkirc \- ultra\-lightweight ELKS\-first IRC client

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B elkirc
.RB [ -d | --debug ]
.RB [ -c | --color ]
.I server port nick

.SH DESCRIPTION
elkirc is a minimal, portable IRC client intended to run on resource-constrained systems (ELKS) while remaining usable on modern platforms.
It uses a single TCP connection and `select()` to multiplex stdin and the network socket.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -d ", " --debug
Enable debug mode. When enabled, PING messages from the server are displayed. By default, PING messages are hidden to reduce clutter.

.TP
.BR -c ", " --color
Enable color output using ANSI escape codes. Colors enhance readability:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Prompt: Channel/nick in orange, brackets in bold
.IP \(bu 2
User messages: Your own messages in bold
.IP \(bu 2
Channel messages: Nicks in blue, brackets in bold
.IP \(bu 2
NOTICE messages: Content after \fB:***\fR in purple (prefix hidden)
.IP \(bu 2
Server numeric replies (matching \fB:server.domain XXX nick \fR pattern):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
0XX/1XX/2XX: Content after "nick " in blue
.IP \(bu 2
3XX (MOTD/NAMES): Content after "nick " in green
.IP \(bu 2
4XX/5XX (errors): Content after "nick " in red
.IP \(bu 2
Prefix \fB:server.domain XXX nick \fR shown only when \fB-d/--debug\fR is enabled (in grey)
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
JOIN messages: Entire message in green
.IP \(bu 2
Other server messages: Messages starting with \fB:\fR in grey
.RE

.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are typed at the prompt (start with a `/`):

.TP
.B /nick <newnick>
Change your nickname.

.TP
.B /join <#channel|nick>
Join a channel or switch to a private target.

.TP
.B /msg <nick> <message>
Send a private message to `nick`.

.TP
.B /raw <text>
Send raw IRC text to the server.

.TP
.B /quit
Send QUIT and exit.

.TP
.B /exit
Exit immediately without sending QUIT.

.SH EXAMPLES
Connect to libera.chat:
.B
elkirc irc.libera.chat 6667 alice

.SH BUGS
Minimal feature set: no IPv6, no TLS, no message history.

